instruction
in Terminal
1.bash run-docker-compose.sh
You're in the docker terminal now.
2.bash install-python-dependencies.sh
3.run-flask-api.sh
The python server is now running.
4.open postman 
5.GET http://0.0.0.0:5000/ 
This should return 'hello stranger!.'
6.POST http://0.0.0.0:5000/hello/<randomname>
This should return 'hello <randomname>!.'
and <randonname> is now saved in data1.db

thank you.